values: Hi everybody. Just wanted to announce I'm moving on to a new journal. I never feel motivated to post about my everyday life here anymore cuz I got better things to do and it's pointless to pretend anything else. The new journal is focused on my work as a comic book artist and being generally creative (which is my new full time job) and if anyone's interested in that, please have a look and add me at   . I'll still be up for talking and staying in touch with people, it's just the posts that'll be a lot more srz bznz oriented and personally I'm very excited about that! Hope to see you there. Else buh bye and thanks.

In other news, on Friday I’m gonna see Benga!!!!

I’m so excited. I don’t know if anyone else is into Dubstep, but it’s the new amazing thing for me. Dark, polished, minimalist and BASS! Lotsa bass. It’s perfect for me right now and for the first time in ages I feel really great about a type of music like that, I just wanna hear everything I can find and learn about it and ahhh! I’ve missed that feeling. I only have two albums (no money, no internet, only Eleen’s crappy ipod ;___;) but they’re great and I think you should all try to find some stuff.

Anyway, Benga is one of the bigger names in Dubstep I suppose and he’s playing in Dublin tomorrow and me and Eleen and her sister and her sister’s boyfriend are going to see him. He’s great. I’m so excited for this, omg! First time in YEARS I’ve been on a concert for a band/artist I liked! Sorry. If I had the net for myself I’d share.

 


Also... HOT!
